JSON\\n  3541→+\\n  3542→+```json\\n  3543→+{\\\"hooks_installed\\\": 3}\\n  3544→+```\\n  3545→+\\n  3546→+#### `uninstall-hooks`\\n  3547→+\\n  3548→+Removes installed agent hooks.\\n  3549→+\\n  3550→+**Arguments:** None\\n  3551→+\\n  3552→+**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n  3553→+\\n  3554→+#### `are-hooks-installed`\\n  3555→+\\n  3556→+Checks whether hooks are currently installed.\\n  3557→+\\n  3558→+**Arguments:** None\\n  3559→+\\n  3560→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3561→+\\n  3562→+```json\\n  3563→+{\\\"installed\\\": true}\\n  3564→+```\\n  3565→+\\n  3566→+### Capability: `transcript_analyzer`\\n  3567→+\\n  3568→+Required when `capabilities.transcript_analyzer` is `true`.\\n  3569→+\\n  3570→+#### `get-transcript-position --path <path>`\\n  3571→+\\n  3572→+Returns the current byte position/size of a transcript file.\\n  3573→+\\n  3574→+**Arguments:**\\n  3575→+- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3576→+\\n  3577→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3578→+\\n  3579→+```json\\n  3580→+{\\\"position\\\": 12345}\\n  3581→+```\\n  3582→+\\n  3583→+#### `extract-modified-files --path <path> --offset <n>`\\n  3584→+\\n  3585→+Extracts the list of files modified by the agent from a transcript.\\n  3586→+\\n  3587→+**Arguments:**\\n  3588→+- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3589→+- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n  3590→+\\n  3591→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3592→+\\n  3593→+```json\\n  3594→+{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"path/to/file1.go\\\", \\\"path/to/file2.go\\\"], \\\"current_position\\\": 12345}\\n  3595→+```\\n  3596→+\\n  3597→+The `current_position` field returns the transcript position after extraction, allowing the caller to resume from that point on subsequent calls.\\n  3598→+\\n  3599→+#### `extract-prompts --session-ref <path> --offset <n>`\\n  3600→+\\n  3601→+Extracts user prompts from a transcript.\\n  3602→+\\n  3603→+**Arguments:**\\n  3604→+- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3605→+- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n  3606→+\\n  3607→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3608→+\\n  3609→+```json\\n  3610→+{\\\"prompts\\\": [\\\"first prompt text\\\", \\\"second prompt text\\\"]}\\n  3611→+```\\n  3612→+\\n  3613→+#### `extract-summary --session-ref <path>`\\n  3614→+\\n  3615→+Extracts an AI-generated summary from a transcript.\\n  3616→+\\n  3617→+**Arguments:**\\n  3618→+- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3619→+\\n  3620→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3621→+\\n  3622→+```json\\n  3623→+{\\\"summary\\\": \\\"Summary text here\\\", \\\"has_summary\\\": true}\\n  3624→+```\\n  3625→+\\n  3626→+### Capability: `transcript_preparer`\\n  3627→+\\n  3628→+Required when `capabilities.transcript_preparer` is `true`.\\n  3629→+\\n  3630→+#### `prepare-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n  3631→+\\n  3632→+Prepares/processes a transcript file (e.g., converting from raw format).\\n  3633→+\\n  3634→+**Arguments:**\\n  3635→+- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3636→+\\n  3637→+**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n  3638→+\\n  3639→+### Capability: `token_calculator`\\n  3640→+\\n  3641→+Required when `capabilities.token_calculator` is `true`.\\n  3642→+\\n  3643→+#### `calculate-tokens --offset <n>`\\n  3644→+\\n  3645→+Calculates token usage from a transcript.\\n  3646→+\\n  3647→+**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n  3648→+\\n  3649→+**Arguments:**\\n  3650→+- `--offset` — Byte offset to start calculating from\\n  3651→+\\n  3652→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3653→+\\n  3654→+```json\\n  3655→+{\\n  3656→+  \\\"input_tokens\\\": 1500,\\n  3657→+  \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 0,\\n  3658→+  \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 200,\\n  3659→+  \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500,\\n  3660→+  \\\"api_call_count\\\": 3,\\n  3661→+  \\\"subagent_tokens\\\": null\\n  3662→+}\\n  3663→+```\\n  3664→+\\n  3665→+Only `input_tokens` and `output_tokens` are required. The optional fields (`cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, `api_call_count`) default to `0` if omitted. `subagent_tokens` is an optional nested object with the same structure, for agents that spawn subagents.\\n  3666→+\\n  3667→+### Capability: `text_generator`\\n  3668→+\\n  3669→+Required when `capabilities.text_generator` is `true`.\\n  3670→+\\n  3671→+#### `generate-text --model <model>`\\n  3672→+\\n  3673→+Generates text using the agent's underlying LLM.\\n  3674→+\\n  3675→+**Input (stdin):** Prompt text.\\n  3676→+\\n  3677→+**Arguments:**\\n  3678→+- `--model` — Model to use for generation\\n  3679→+\\n  3680→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3681→+\\n  3682→+```json\\n  3683→+{\\\"text\\\": \\\"Generated response text\\\"}\\n  3684→+```\\n  3685→+\\n  3686→+### Capability: `hook_response_writer`\\n  3687→+\\n  3688→+Required when `capabilities.hook_response_writer` is `true`.\\n  3689→+\\n  3690→+#### `write-hook-response --message <message>`\\n  3691→+\\n  3692→+Writes a message in the agent's native hook response format.\\n  3693→+\\n  3694→+**Arguments:**\\n  3695→+- `--message` — Message to write\\n  3696→+\\n  3697→+**Output (stdout):** Agent-native format bytes (e.g., JSONL for Claude Code).\\n  3698→+\\n  3699→+### Capability: `subagent_aware_extractor`\\n  3700→+\\n  3701→+Required when `capabilities.subagent_aware_extractor` is `true`.\\n  3702→+\\n  3703→+#### `extract-all-modified-files --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n  3704→+\\n  3705→+Extracts modified files from both the main transcript and any subagent transcripts.\\n  3706→+\\n  3707→+**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n  3708→+\\n  3709→+**Arguments:**\\n  3710→+- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n  3711→+- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n  3712→+\\n  3713→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3714→+\\n  3715→+```json\\n  3716→+{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"file1.go\\\", \\\"file2.go\\\"]}\\n  3717→+```\\n  3718→+\\n  3719→+#### `calculate-total-tokens --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n  3720→+\\n  3721→+Calculates total token usage across main transcript and subagent transcripts.\\n  3722→+\\n  3723→+**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n  3724→+\\n  3725→+**Arguments:**\\n  3726→+- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n  3727→+- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n  3728→+\\n  3729→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3730→+\\n  3731→+```json\\n  3732→+{\\n  3733→+  \\\"input_tokens\\\": 5000,\\n  3734→+  \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 0,\\n  3735→+  \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 1000,\\n  3736→+  \\\"output_tokens\\\": 2000,\\n  3737→+  \\\"api_call_count\\\": 8,\\n  3738→+  \\\"subagent_tokens\\\": {\\n  3739→+    \\\"input_tokens\\\": 2000,\\n  3740→+    \\\"output_tokens\\\": 800\\n  3741→+  }\\n  3742→+}\\n  3743→+```\\n  3744→+\\n  3745→+Same token usage format as `calculate-tokens`. The `subagent_tokens` field aggregates usage from all subagents.\\n  3746→+\\n  3747→+## Shared Object Definitions\\n  3748→+\\n  3749→+### HookInput Object\\n  3750→+\\n  3751→+The HookInput object is passed via stdin to `get-session-id` and `read-session`.\\n  3752→+\\n  3753→+```json\\n  3754→+{\\n  3755→+  \\\"hook_type\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n  3756→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3757→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n  3758→+  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  3759→+  \\\"user_prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the login bug\\\",\\n  3760→+  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n  3761→+  \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"toolu_abc123\\\",\\n  3762→+  \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/src/main.go\\\"},\\n  3763→+  \\\"raw_data\\\": {\\\"custom_field\\\": \\\"value\\\"}\\n  3764→+}\\n  3765→+```\\n  3766→+\\n  3767→+| Field | Type | Description |\\n  3768→+|---|---|---|\\n  3769→+| `hook_type` | string | Hook type: `session_start`, `session_end`, `user_prompt_submit`, `stop`, `pre_tool_use`, `post_tool_use` |\\n  3770→+| `session_id` | string | Agent session identifier |\\n  3771→+| `session_ref` | string | Agent-specific session reference (typically a file path) |\\n  3772→+| `timestamp` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp |\\n  3773→+| `user_prompt` | string | User's prompt text (from `user_prompt_submit` hooks). Optional. |\\n  3774→+| `tool_name` | string | Tool name (from `pre_tool_use`/`post_tool_use` hooks). Optional. |\\n  3775→+| `tool_use_id` | string | Tool invocation ID. Optional. |\\n  3776→+| `tool_input` | object | Raw tool input JSON. Optional. |\\n  3777→+| `raw_data` | object | Agent-specific data for extension. Optional. |\\n  3778→+\\n  3779→+### AgentSession Object\\n  3780→+\\n  3781→+Used as input to `write-session` and output from `read-session`.\\n  3782→+\\n  3783→+```json\\n  3784→+{\\n  3785→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3786→+  \\\"agent_name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  3787→+  \\\"repo_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n  3788→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n  3789→+  \\\"start_time\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  3790→+  \\\"native_data\\\": null,\\n  3791→+  \\\"modified_files\\\": [\\\"src/main.go\\\"],\\n  3792→+  \\\"new_files\\\": [\\\"src/new_file.go\\\"],\\n  3793→+  \\\"deleted_files\\\": []\\n  3794→+}\\n  3795→+```\\n  3796→+\\n  3797→+| Field | Type | Description |\\n  3798→+|---|---|---|\\n  3799→+| `session_id` | string | Agent session identifier |\\n  3800→+| `agent_name` | string | Agent registry name |\\n  3801→+| `repo_path` | string | Absolute path to the repository |\\n  3802→+| `session_ref` | string | Path/reference to session in agent's storage |\\n  3803→+| `start_time` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp of session start |\\n  3804→+| `native_data` | bytes/null | Session content in agent's native format (opaque to CLI) |\\n  3805→+| `modified_files` | string[] | Files modified during the session |\\n  3806→+| `new_files` | string[] | Files created during the session |\\n  3807→+| `deleted_files` | string[] | Files deleted during the session |\\n  3808→+\\n  3809→+### Event Object\\n  3810→+\\n  3811→+Returned by `parse-hook`. Represents a normalized lifecycle event.\\n  3812→+\\n  3813→+```json\\n  3814→+{\\n  3815→+  \\\"type\\\": 3,\\n  3816→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3817→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n  3818→+  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the login bug\\\",\\n  3819→+  \\\"model\\\": \\\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\\\",\\n  3820→+  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\"\\n  3821→+}\\n  3822→+```\\n  3823→+\\n  3824→+| Field | Type | Description |\\n  3825→+|---|---|---|\\n  3826→+| `type` | int | **Required.** Event type (see table below) |\\n  3827→+| `session_id` | string | **Required.** Agent session identifier |\\n  3828→+| `previous_session_id` | string | Non-empty when this event represents a session continuation/handoff. Optional. |\\n  3829→+| `session_ref` | string | Agent-specific transcript reference. Optional. |\\n  3830→+| `prompt` | string | User's prompt text (on `TurnStart` events). Optional. |\\n  3831→+| `model` | string | LLM model identifier. Optional. |\\n  3832→+| `timestamp` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp. Optional. |\\n  3833→+| `tool_use_id` | string | Tool invocation ID (for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n  3834→+| `subagent_id` | string | Subagent instance ID (for `SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n  3835→+| `tool_input` | object | Raw tool input JSON (for subagent type/description extraction). Optional. |\\n  3836→+| `subagent_type` | string | Kind of subagent (for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n  3837→+| `task_description` | string | Subagent task description. Optional. |\\n  3838→+| `response_message` | string | Message to display to the user via the agent. Optional. |\\n  3839→+| `metadata` | object | Agent-specific state preserved across events. Optional. |\\n  3840→+\\n  3841→+**Event types:**\\n  3842→+\\n  3843→+| Value | Name | Description |\\n  3844→+|---|---|---|\\n  3845→+| 1 | SessionStart | Agent session has begun |\\n  3