",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"dccb059e-a37d-4287-9fa3-471a6aa16f44\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hugging-cherny\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T09:18:08.699Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_016boVkMDtkXCdbXr1ow9aeu\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01MonM5yCZ2ehLS3ZX3sF1DU\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli/docs/requirements/external-plugins/review-02.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 02\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-03-05\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\\n\\n## Previous Review Status\\n\\n- [x] Issue 1 from review-01: Unbounded `io.ReadAll` in `ParseHookEvent` - FIXED (now uses `io.LimitReader` with 10MB cap at line 211-212)\\n- [ ] Issue 3 from review-01: Many methods use `context.Background()` - STILL OUTSTANDING (acknowledged as interface limitation)\\n- [x] Issue 4 from review-01: Discovery timeout context concern - STILL VALID but acceptable as documented\\n- [ ] Issue 5 from review-01: Agent name from filename not validated - STILL OUTSTANDING\\n- [ ] Issue 6 from review-01: `cmd.Environ()` inherits full parent environment - STILL OUTSTANDING (documentation gap)\\n- [ ] Issue 7 from review-01: No stdout buffer size limit - STILL OUTSTANDING\\n- [ ] Issue 11 from review-01: Unchecked `EventType` cast - STILL OUTSTANDING\\n- [ ] Issue 12 from review-01: Silent empty-string returns with no logging - STILL OUTSTANDING\\n- [ ] Issue 13 from review-01: Discovery runs on every hook invocation - STILL OUTSTANDING\\n\\n## New Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\n1. **[`cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`:31-33] `DiscoverAndRegister` runs during command tree construction, not during command execution**\\n\\n   `newHooksCmd()` is called during `root.go` initialization (line 82: `cmd.AddCommand(newHooksCmd())`). This means `DiscoverAndRegister` runs on EVERY `entire` CLI invocation, including `entire version`, `entire status`, etc. -- not just hook-related commands. This adds process-spawning overhead to every CLI call when `external_agents` is enabled.\\n\\n   The discovery should be deferred until the hooks command is actually executed, or at minimum until it is known that a hooks subcommand will run. Consider moving discovery into a `PersistentPreRunE` on the hooks command, or using Cobra's lazy initialization.\\n\\n   ```go\\n   cmd := &cobra.Command{\\n       Use: \\\"hooks\\\",\\n       PersistentPreRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\\n           discoveryCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(cmd.Context(), 5*time.Second)\\n           defer cancel()\\n           external.DiscoverAndRegister(discoveryCtx)\\n           return nil\\n       },\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n   Note: This also affects `enable` -- external agents are NOT discoverable during `entire enable` because `setup.go` does not call `DiscoverAndRegister`. If external agents should be selectable during setup, discovery needs to happen there too.\\n\\n2. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`:428] No limit on stdout buffer -- reiteration of review-01 issue 7**\\n\\n   `cmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf` still collects unbounded output from the external binary. Since `ParseHookEvent` now limits stdin (good), the equivalent protection for stdout is missing. A buggy or malicious external agent could cause OOM by writing excessive output. This is the last remaining unbounded I/O path.\\n\\n   Suggested fix: Use a `LimitedWriter` or check `stdoutBuf.Len()` after `cmd.Run()` returns:\\n\\n   ```go\\n   const maxStdoutBytes = 50 * 1024 * 1024 // 50 MB\\n   cmd.Stdout = &limitedBuffer{buf: &stdoutBuf, limit: maxStdoutBytes}\\n   ```\\n\\n   Or simpler (post-hoc check):\\n\\n   ```go\\n   if stdoutBuf.Len() > maxStdoutBytes {\\n       return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"%s: output too large (%d bytes)\\\", args[0], stdoutBuf.Len())\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n3. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/discovery.go`:55] Agent name validation still missing (review-01 issue 5)**\\n\\n   The agent name from the filename is still used without validation. A binary named `entire-agent-` (empty suffix) would register an agent with an empty name. A binary named `entire-agent-foo bar` (space in name) would register with a space in the name. These edge cases could cause unexpected behavior in the registry and command tree.\\n\\n   This is a simple fix with high value:\\n\\n   ```go\\n   import \\\"regexp\\\"\\n\\n   var validAgentName = regexp.MustCompile(`^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$`)\\n\\n   // In the loop:\\n   nameStr := strings.TrimPrefix(name, binaryPrefix)\\n   if !validAgentName.MatchString(nameStr) {\\n       continue\\n   }\\n   agentName := types.AgentName(nameStr)\\n   ```\\n\\n4. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`:123-137, 150-161, 189-195] Silent failures return zero-values without logging**\\n\\n   `GetSessionID`, `ResolveSessionFile`, and `FormatResumeCommand` all swallow errors and return empty strings. While this matches the built-in agent interface contract, external agent failures are much more likely (binary crashes, protocol mismatches, timeouts) and much harder to debug without logging. At minimum, add `logging.Debug` calls to these error paths. This was raised in review-01 (issue 12) and is still unaddressed.\\n\\n5. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/types.go`:148-150] `eventJSON.toEvent()` does not validate `EventType` range**\\n\\n   The `Type` field is cast directly: `Type: agent.EventType(ej.Type)`. An external agent returning `\\\"type\\\": 0` or `\\\"type\\\": 999` would create an event with an unknown type that propagates through the lifecycle handler. This could cause silent no-ops or panics depending on how the lifecycle code handles unknown event types.\\n\\n   Suggested fix:\\n\\n   ```go\\n   if ej.Type < 1 || ej.Type > 7 {\\n       return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"unknown event type: %d\\\", ej.Type)\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n6. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external_test.go`:36-101] Mock script JSON injection fragility (review-01 issue 8)**\\n\\n   `mockInfoScript` concatenates JSON directly into a shell `echo` command with single quotes. If any test ever passes JSON containing a single quote, the shell script will break silently (malformed output, not a test failure). This is currently safe but fragile.\\n\\n   Consider writing JSON to a temp file and having the script `cat` it:\\n\\n   ```go\\n   func mockInfoScript(infoJSON string) string {\\n       // Write JSON to a file to avoid shell quoting issues\\n       return `#!/bin/sh\\n   case \\\"$1\\\" in\\n     info) cat \\\"$0.json\\\" ;;\\n     ...\\n   ```\\n\\n   Or use a heredoc approach.\\n\\n7. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/discovery_test.go`:66-104] Discovery tests modify global agent registry without cleanup**\\n\\n   Tests like `TestDiscoverAndRegister_FindsAgent` register agents in the global `agent` registry but never unregister them. Since these tests cannot use `t.Parallel()` (they modify process-global state), the registered agents leak into subsequent tests in the same file. This could cause false positives in `TestDiscoverAndRegister_SkipsNameConflict` if run order changes.\\n\\n   The agent registry does not appear to have an `Unregister` function, so this may need one added for test hygiene, or tests should use unique agent names that won't collide (which they currently do via distinct name strings -- so the risk is low but worth noting).\\n\\n### Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n8. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/capabilities.go`:30-88] As* helpers are highly repetitive**\\n\\n   All seven `As*` functions follow the exact same pattern: type-assert, check `CapabilityDeclarer`, return. Consider a generic helper to reduce duplication:\\n\\n   ```go\\n   func asCapability[T any](ag Agent, capCheck func(DeclaredCaps) bool) (T, bool) {\\n       t, ok := any(ag).(T)\\n       if !ok {\\n           var zero T\\n           return zero, false\\n       }\\n       if cd, ok := ag.(CapabilityDeclarer); ok {\\n           return t, capCheck(cd.DeclaredCapabilities())\\n       }\\n       return t, true\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n   This would reduce ~90 lines to ~15. However, the current explicit approach has the advantage of being very readable and grep-friendly. This is purely a style preference.\\n\\n9. **[`docs/architecture/external-agent-protocol.md`] Protocol doc should mention environment inheritance**\\n\\n   As noted in review-01 issue 6, external agents receive the full parent process environment. The protocol doc should explicitly state this so plugin authors know not to leak sensitive environment variables. Add a note to the \\\"Environment\\\" section:\\n\\n   > In addition to the variables listed above, the external binary inherits the full environment of the calling process. Plugin authors should be aware that environment variables like API keys and tokens may be present.\\n\\n10. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`:346-348] `New()` does not validate `info.Name` matches the binary name**\\n\\n    The `info` response includes a `name` field, but `DiscoverAndRegister` uses the binary filename to derive the agent name, not the `info.Name`. If `entire-agent-foo` returns `{\\\"name\\\": \\\"bar\\\"}`, the agent is registered as `foo` (from the filename) but internally reports its name as `bar` (from info). This mismatch could confuse users when the name shown in `entire status` differs from the binary name.\\n\\n    Consider either: (a) validating they match, or (b) documenting that the binary filename is the authoritative name and `info.name` is just a display hint.\\n\\n11. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`:97-98] `ReadTranscript` does not limit the response size**\\n\\n    `ReadTranscript` returns the raw stdout bytes without any size cap. For a transcript file, this could be tens or hundreds of megabytes. While the timeout provides some protection, a fast external agent could still write a large amount of data within the 30-second window. Consider adding a size limit or at least documenting the expectation.\\n\\n### Praise\\n\\n- **Issue 1 from review-01 was properly addressed**: The `ParseHookEvent` now correctly uses `io.LimitReader` with a 10MB cap. Good fix.\\n\\n- **Consistent `As*` migration**: The refactoring from direct type assertions to capability-aware helpers is complete and consistent across all 15+ call sites in `lifecycle.go`, `state.go`, `setup.go`, `config.go`, `hook_registry.go`, `hooks_cmd.go`, and `strategy/` files. No call sites were missed.\\n\\n- **`wrappedAgent` compile-time interface checks**: The `var _ agent.X = (*wrappedAgent)(nil)` lines at the bottom of `capabilities.go` ensure all interfaces are satisfied at compile time. Good practice.\\n\\n- **Test coverage is thorough**: The discovery tests cover 8 scenarios (find, dedup, name conflict, non-executable, directory, disabled, empty PATH, unreadable dir, info failure). The capability tests cover all 7 optional interfaces with 3 variants each (not implemented, declared true, declared false). The external agent tests cover identity, detect, session operations, transcript operations, hooks, error handling, timeout behavior, and all capability wrapping combinations.\\n\\n- **Protocol documentation is comprehensive**: The `external-agent-protocol.md` document is well-structured with clear tables, JSON examples, and complete coverage of all subcommands and shared object definitions.\\n\\n- **`PrepareTranscript` added to `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript`**: The new code block at `manual_commit_hooks.go`:1488-1501 adds transcript preparation before file extraction during active sessions. This fixes a real bug where OpenCode transcripts might not be flushed before the strategy tries to read modified files from them.\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n**Overall assessment: REQUEST CHANGES**\\n\\nThe implementation quality is high and the architecture is sound. Most feedback from review-01 was acknowledged, and the critical `io.ReadAll` issue was properly fixed. However, two issues remain that should be addressed before merge:\\n\\n**Key concerns:**\\n1. **Discovery runs on every CLI invocation** (new critical finding) -- this adds unnecessary overhead to non-hook commands like `entire version`. Move discovery to a lazy/deferred path.\\n2. **No stdout buffer limit** (carried from review-01) -- the last unbounded I/O path from external binaries.\\n3. **Agent name validation** (carried from review-01) -- simple fix, prevents edge cases with empty or malformed names.\\n\\n**Estimated effort to address feedback:**\\n- Critical fixes (items 1-2): ~1-2 hours\\n- Important fixes (items 3-5): ~1 hour\\n- Suggestions: optional, can be follow-up\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":382,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":90823,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":382},\"output_tokens\":25,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYjgV6t2LRi1p9wkSPqd9\",\"uuid\":\"3c6de6d1-a2e3-4645-a277-2f1c6e5bff7e\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"acf8d786c4bdadd9e\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_012DXLQTpm4TaVJmo93oGb44\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Y7S6hEkU5EgFjKc8gd89uT\",\"uuid\":\"3221f170-6e1a-42fc-97a5-db2609ede5db\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T09:18:08.700Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3221f170-6e1a-42fc-97a5-db2609ede5db\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"dccb059e-a37d-4287-9fa3-471a6aa16f44\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"dele